</section>

<!-- INFO SECTION -->
<section class="float-info">
  <h2 class="float-info__heading">The price of a floating session is €40, duration 1 hour.</h2>
  <p>To ensure your floating session is as pleasant and relaxing as possible, we recommend arriving at least 15 minutes before the session begins. This will give you enough time for us to explain how the floating process works and to take a shower beforehand.</p>
  <p>Our floating sessions take place in silence and privacy. You can choose whether you prefer to float in complete darkness or use a soft ambient light. The choice is yours; we want your experience to be exactly as you wish!</p>
  <p>We also welcome individuals with mobility challenges. To ensure a comfortable experience, we recommend contacting us before your visit.</p>
  <p><strong>What is available on site:</strong> towel, bathrobe, slippers, shower gel, shampoo and hairdryer.</p>
  <p><strong>Who floating is for:</strong> those under stress or on the verge of burnout, athletes for recovery, expectant mothers (it relieves pressure on the back and legs), those with chronic back pain and muscle tension, and anyone who wants better sleep.</p>
  <p><strong>Who floating is not for:</strong> in case of uncontrolled epilepsy, fresh wounds or scratches, infectious diseases, and while under the influence of alcohol or drugs.</p>
  <p>If you have more questions about floating, see our <a href="/en/faq" class="float-info__link">frequently asked questions</a></p>
</section>

